# Content & Privacy

## File layout

| Locale | Blog | Portfolio | Pages |
|--------|------|-----------|-------|
| EN | `content/blog/*.md` | `content/portfolio/*.md` | `content/pages/*.md` |
| DE | `content/de/blog/*.md` | `content/de/portfolio/*.md` | `content/de/pages/*.md` |

Schema defined in `content.config.ts`. Blog posts support `draft: true` (hidden from listing).

## Frontmatter

**Blog**: `title`, `description`, `date`, `tags`, `draft`, `ai_assist` (optional)
**Portfolio**: `title`, `description`, `date`, `cover`, `tech`, `featured`, `link`, `draft`, `ai_assist` (optional)
**Pages**: `title`, `description`, `draft`

Set `draft: true` until the author confirms publish. Both blog and portfolio listings hide drafts.

### AI disclosure (`ai_assist`)

Record honestly how AI helped: `drafting`, `editing`, `translation`, `code`, `research`, `images`. See [`AI-USAGE.md`](../AI-USAGE.md) for definitions. Not rendered on posts yet — metadata for transparency in git.

## Privacy — never commit

Content in git is public-facing — including `draft: true` posts. Same rules apply to portfolio items and all markdown in the repo.

- Real company name, address, employees, customers, suppliers
- Private manufacturing app names, ERP/RPS data, production figures
- Anything identifying a specific German manufacturing business

See [`.cursor/public-repo-standards.md`](../public-repo-standards.md).

## Safe storytelling

- "A small metal manufacturing company" / "my shopfloor"
- Abstract lessons: learning to code while running a business, AI as a multiplier
- WERKSCODE as the public brand; anonymized composites instead of real incidents
- When unsure, ask the author before including a detail
